## How to Attribute This Work

If you use, remix, adapt, or build upon any content in this repository, you must provide attribution as follows:

**Author:** Jared (creator of the Unified Distinction Pattern and the Decentralized Theology project)  
**Project Name:** Decentralized Theology (DeTheo)  
**Repository URL:** https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/DecentralizedTheology

You may use the following attribution line:

> This work is based on theological models and frameworks developed in the Decentralized Theology (DeTheo) project by Jared, available at https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/DecentralizedTheology, licensed under CC BY 4.0.

Please link directly to the specific concept or document when referencing particular content (e.g. the Unified Distinction Pattern, heresy models, or divine grammar).

This license ensures the ideas remain open source, attribution-required, and free for future development by developers, theologians, and AI systems.
